INSERT INTO `content_field_body` VALUES (4,4,'<p>In <strong>one business day</strong> this could be your website. <em>No really, it could...</em> <strong>Watershed Now!</strong> is a free and open source <a href=\"http://drupal.org\" target=\"_blank\">Drupal</a> distribution developed to support the common content management, social media, online advocacy, fundraising, and geo-mapping needs of conservation organizations, such as watershed groups, land trusts, and environmental chapter organizations.</p><p>Out of the box, Watershed Now! packs a punch - with all the tools your organization needs to quickly build its presence online. As your organization grows, Watershed Now! serves as a great platform for quickly and affordably building out a more customized website with beautiful graphic design and powerful messaging.</p><p>To learn more about Watershed Now!, you&#39;re best off just taking this demo site for a test drive. Click around and see what Watershed Now! can do. If you like it, we can <a href=\"/contact\">schedule you a tour</a> of the backend administrative interface. (It&#39;s really easy to drive this application, and we know you are going to love it.)</p><p>A complete listing of Watershed Now!&#39;s features can be found on our <a href=\"http://drupal.org/project/watershednow\" target=\"_blank\">Drupal.org project page</a>. To download your own copy of Watershed Now!, check us out on <a href=\"http://github.com/thinkshout/watershednow\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub</a>.</p>',2),(5,5,'<p>(Oh, by the way, this is a sample blog post.)</p><p>Posterous.com is a free 3rd-party service that lets you email content to all of your social media services, such as Faceboo, Twitter, YouTube, Flickr, and Watershed Now!.</p><p>When you create an account with Posterous, it provides you with an email address that only you and your team can use to post content to the web. Posterous allows you to attach raw photos and video files to your email posts as well and it will process them for playback on the web.</p><p>This means that when you are busy out in the field monitoring streams, leading conservation or restoration projects, or stopping polluters, you can post multimedia content to your blog straight from you phone.</p>',2),(6,6,'<p><span class=\"field-content\">(Oh, by the way, this is a sample blog post.) </span>Why yes, you can! Watershed Now! provides RSS feeds of all you blog posts and events listings. Any website that call pull in RSS feeds can receive your posts.</p><p>But even cooler than that, Watershed Now! provides you with custom &quot;website badgets&quot; (little snippets of pre-generated code) that allow your site visitors and supports to post dynamic listings of your content on their own web pages.</p><p>In other words, with Watershed Now!, your supporters can place a &quot;Donate Now&quot; badge on their own websites and social media pages that help you raise money and/or call your community to action.</p>',2),(7,7,'<p><span class=\"field-content\">(Oh, by the way, this is a sample blog post.) </span>Well, you are right. A lot of the sweetness of Watershed Now! lives under the hood. We&#39;ll need to give you a logged-in tour to show you all of that stuff. And, to be totally transparent, we&#39;re still building out some of the little helper features that would allow a non-technical person to get Watershed Now! up and running in just a few clicks. Watershed Now! still takes a bit of developer time to install and configure. That said, Watershed Now! creators at ThinkShout.com are using the v0.1 release of the application to build out all of the new conservation websites that we are building from clients. Leveraging Watershed Now! in its current form, we&#39;ve been able to reduce the production time and client costs of these websites substantially.</p>',2),(1,1,'<p>[This is a placeholder &quot;About Us&quot; page. With Watershed Now!, you can manage an unlimited amount of content describing the important work of your organization. Create and edit pages, add them to the hierarchical menu structure. Build a library of information describing your organization&#39;s critical efforts to conserve, protect, and restore our natural resources.]</p>',2),(3,3,'<p>[This is a placeholder &quot;History&quot; page in the &quot;About Us&quot; section. With Watershed Now!, you can manage an unlimited amount of content describing the important work of your organization. Create and edit pages, add them to the hierarchical menu structure. Build a library of information describing your organization&#39;s critical efforts to conserve, protect, and restore our natural resources.]</p>',2),(2,2,'<p>[This is a placeholder &quot;Staff&quot; page in the &quot;About Us&quot; section. With Watershed Now!, you can manage an unlimited amount of content describing the important work of your organization. Create and edit pages, add them to the hierarchical menu structure. Build a library of information describing your organization&#39;s critical efforts to conserve, protect, and restore our natural resources.]</p>',2),(8,8,'<p>Join Water Words that Work and ThinkShout.com for our upcoming &quot;Website Sprint&quot;!</p><p>This is a sample event posting. See the sign-up form below? Please don&#39;t try to use it to get in touch with us about the sprint, but it&#39;s here as an example of how the event management tool works for Watershed Now!</p><p>Create events a start date/time (and optional end date/time). Then, if you want, you can enable these events to support site visitor sign-ups. When sign-ups enabled, you can set registration limits, send out automated event reminders, and even send broadcast email to registrants whenever you want.</p>',2),(9,9,'<p>[This is a sample &quot;Take Action&quot; e-petition. Your submissions will not be sent to anyone, so feel free to play.]</p><h2>Save the Internet, Save the World!</h2><p>Well, actually this is a real campaign issue for us geeks. If you are curious sometime, check out NTEN&#39;s updates on <a href=\"http://www.nten.org/blog/2010/04/30/save-internet-save-world\" target=\"_blank\">Net Neutrality</a>. But for now, just have fun with the form below. We aren&#39;t going to send your responses anywhere.</p>',2);
